abstract: TALLMAN, N. Y., Dec. 22 -Way Out Man, an 8-year-old brown gelding owned and ridden by Michael Cody of Greenwich, Conn., captured the open jumper championship at the Cherry Lane Stable's horse show today.

abstract: DETROIT, Dec. 20 -- On the basis of what happened tonight at Cobo Arena, the New York Knickerbockers did exactly the right thing yesterday when they traded Walt Bellamy and Howie (Butch) Komives to the Pistons for Dave DeBusschere.
